From Hollister.Jeff at epamail.epa.gov  Wed Apr 16 17:12:05 2008
From: Hollister.Jeff at epamail.epa.gov (Hollister.Jeff at epamail.epa.gov)
Date: Wed, 16 Apr 2008 11:12:05 -0400
Subject: [R-sig-eco] Welcome All
Message-ID: <OFC651CCB4.0B2421B3-ON8525742D.0052BE09-8525742D.00538123@epamail.epa.gov>


I was a little concerned that we would not have enough interest to
sustain a list on R in Ecology.  Evidently my concern was unfounded.

Within the first hour or so nearly 60 people have signed up.

I look forward to the discussions/questions/etc to come.

Again, I view this list as a place for ecologists to seek and provide
advice, assistance, ideas, announcements (i.e. new scripts, books, etc.)
on R in ecology.  Through this, I think we can increase the number of
ecologists using R.  Lastly, I hope that posting to R-sig-ecology will
be slightly less daunting than posting questions to the larger R-help
list and towards that end, I encourage all who have an interest to take
part.

So as a first step, please feel free to extend and invitation to anyone
whom you feel would benefit from this list.

Cheers,
Jeff

